The paper proposes a neural graph model for understanding video data, which involves processing information in both space and time domains. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the proposed model involves neural networks and message passing, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions that the model could learn to recognize high-level spatio-temporal concepts, which could be related to neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on video recognition tasks, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM).
